Other forms of Maha Devi are also worshiped in this festival. It varies according to traditions and beliefs. Vaishnava devotees worship Goddess Lakshmi, while Dravidians worship forms like Kali, Mariamman, Tripurasundari. Many Dravidian devotees celebrate Golu festival. Bengali devotees perform Durgotsava instead of Navadurga worship.
